{"TopicId":111158,"ForumId":46,"TopicTitle":"Ask the Mods questions about the Forums!","CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-28T17:01:51Z","PageNum":149,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T17:16:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533920159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, make your query/search more specific\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, the search engine for this particular forum software is borked. It\u0027s not a kSP forum issue.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T17:31:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431391\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533921382\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, the search engine for this particular forum software is borked. It\u0027s not a kSP forum issue.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaking the search more specific let the search complete.\u00A0 See my previous post\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T18:39:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533920244\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269224\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cydonian Monk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Cydonian Monk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately it does it for any string including Unity. My original search was for \u0022Unity Asset Store\u0022, but it choked on that too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, the forum software\u0027s not very nimble about managing searches.\u00A0 Your search \u0022Unity Asset Store\u0022, if you do it, by default shows \u0022All posts that contain the word \u0027unity\u0027, or the word \u0027asset\u0027, or the word \u0027store\u0027, anywhere in the forum including the gigantic noise archive that is Forum Games and so forth.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe solution is to narrow the search, as folks have mentioned.\u00A0 There are a few ways to do this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESearch for the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ephrase\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 \u003C/strong\u003EWhen you type your search term in the box, put \u0022Unity Asset Store\u0022 \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ein quotes\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 That will tell the search page \u0022look for the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ephrase\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E \u0027Unity Asset Store\u0027 and don\u0027t just try to get every page that has even one of those words.\u0022\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESearch in a \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Especific forum only\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 \u003C/strong\u003EFor example, if you\u0027re searching for something that involves modeling, you could run a search and tell it to search \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eonly the Modeling \u0026amp; Texturing Support sub-forum\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E, rather than the entire KSP forum.\u00A0 By doing this, you are \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Egreatly\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E shrinking the size of the haystack, so finding a particular needle becomes faster.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDo a titles-only search, if you can.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0 May not be applicable to your particular search-- e.g. it would only help you in finding posts that are \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eabout\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E the Unity Asset Store, rather than any posts that merely \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Emention\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E it.\u00A0 So a search like this might not suit your purposes.\u00A0 However, if it \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Edoes\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E... doing title-only searches is \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eway\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E faster than \u0022titles and content\u0022, because the search engine has much much less content to rummage through.\u00A0 It can \u0022skim\u0022, as it were.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nSearching by author is also pretty quick, though that only works if you know which author to search for, which I\u0027m guessing wouldn\u0027t apply in your current case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T14:28:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533926384\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, Snark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, the forum software\u0027s not very nimble about managing searches.\u00A0 Your search \u0022Unity Asset Store\u0022, if you do it, by default shows \u0022All posts that contain the word \u0027unity\u0027, or the word \u0027asset\u0027, or the word \u0027store\u0027, anywhere in the forum including the gigantic noise archive that is Forum Games and so forth.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe solution is to narrow the search, as folks have mentioned.\u00A0 There are a few ways to do this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESearch for the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ephrase\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 \u003C/strong\u003EWhen you type your search term in the box, put \u0022Unity Asset Store\u0022 \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ein quotes\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 That will tell the search page \u0022look for the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Ephrase\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E \u0027Unity Asset Store\u0027 and don\u0027t just try to get every page that has even one of those words.\u0022\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESearch in a \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Especific forum only\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 \u003C/strong\u003EFor example, if you\u0027re searching for something that involves modeling, you could run a search and tell it to search \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eonly the Modeling \u0026amp; Texturing Support sub-forum\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E, rather than the entire KSP forum.\u00A0 By doing this, you are \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Egreatly\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E shrinking the size of the haystack, so finding a particular needle becomes faster.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDo a titles-only search, if you can.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0 May not be applicable to your particular search-- e.g. it would only help you in finding posts that are \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eabout\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E the Unity Asset Store, rather than any posts that merely \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Emention\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E it.\u00A0 So a search like this might not suit your purposes.\u00A0 However, if it \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Edoes\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E... doing title-only searches is \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Eway\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E faster than \u0022titles and content\u0022, because the search engine has much much less content to rummage through.\u00A0 It can \u0022skim\u0022, as it were.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nSearching by author is also pretty quick, though that only works if you know which author to search for, which I\u0027m guessing wouldn\u0027t apply in your current case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431397\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533922307\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaking the search more specific let the search complete.\u00A0 See my previous post\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a walk-around and works quite well in Google and Bing. I\u0027m not sure about other search engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003Exxx\u003C/strong\u003E site:forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com (where \u003Cstrong\u003Exxx\u003C/strong\u003E is your keyword search).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, if I wanted to search for Snark, it would be Snark site:forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com which would yield the following results in Bing:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.bing.com/search?q=\u002BSnark\u002Bsite%3Aforum.kerbalspaceprogram.com\u0026amp;pc=MOZI\u0026amp;form=MOZLBR\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.bing.com/search?q=\u002BSnark\u002Bsite%3Aforum.kerbalspaceprogram.com\u0026amp;amp;pc=MOZI\u0026amp;amp;form=MOZLBR\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyhow, this is how I\u0027ve been searching the forum since the software change. I\u0027m sorry I forgot to mention it\u00A0 in my previous post.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T04:34:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223431920\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533997726\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/11/2018 at 10:28 AM, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003Exxx\u003C/strong\u003E site:forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI searched for XXX, and was very disappointed at the results.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, If I have to do a fairly deep search on the forums, using this trick on Google is the way I do it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MDZhB","CreatedById":99243,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T22:18:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis might have been asked before, but what is the most frequently posted in forum or subforum? What\u0027s the most frequently viewed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-13T23:37:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont face=\u0022Lucida Sans Unicode, Lucida Grande, sans-serif\u0022\u003EPlease may the Emoticon and\u00A0Spoiler\u00A0buttons be more\u00A0different?? I keep\u00A0getting them mixed up.\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-14T06:53:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/185809-hansonkerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022185809\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/185809-hansonkerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@HansonKerman\u003C/a\u003E, if you are using a desktop or laptop to access the forum, you can hold the mouse over the icon for a moment and it will tell you what the button does before you press it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust remember it\u0027s \u0022Face for faces\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-15T21:16:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223433382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534198709\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299243\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MDZhB\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/13/2018 at 6:18 PM, MDZhB said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis might have been asked before, but what is the most frequently posted in forum or subforum? What\u0027s the most frequently viewed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t have had statistics for this, but my gut is telling me that KSP Discussion or Add-On Discussions are the most-viewed and posted-in subforums.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-16T01:46:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223432952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022111158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534134867\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/12/2018 at 11:34 PM, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI searched for XXX, and was very disappointed at the results.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, If I have to do a fairly deep search on the forums, using this trick on Google is the way I do it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca 